annotation.TEXT: Oh, I hope there's something good down there!

Oh, what's this? I somehow didn't see that ledge up there the first two times, and my athletic peach should allow me to get up there... But, I'm falling just short. I guess I'll need a little help from the chairmen of the board here.
There's that glitched "5-up" symbol, which looks different than usual.
Well, here's a door, which is good, so that I can escape that murderous Flying Wiggler. Too bad I couldn't star-kill enough things to get any 1-ups.
And now, let's play the waiting game...
They're still wonky as heck to try to spin jump off of, though, so I'll just use this Boo instead.
It means something like "ghost house"... Well, I was told it could mean "deserted house". Also, some things are possessed? Oh, boy...
RUN AWAY!!! DESPAWN THEM SOMEHOW!!!
Yeah, I saw that 1-up to the left. Totally not worth it to me.
Hmm... While there may be flammable and inflammable things here, I think I want to keep my athletic peach for now.
Whoa, what the...? Umm... Okay, a Boo flew out of that block and left the screen, and that's about it...
1-ups earned this time: 5.75. Bonus game average so far: 61.69 / 8 = 7.71125 1-ups each.
والآن، والسرعة مثيرة للسخرية لعبة مكافأة!
Blue shell = Wigglers Dwelling. Red shell = Haioku.
Uh, yep. See that chair, and how it's floating there in the air? Totally saw that coming (though I was unsure of how it would move, so I'm lucky it didn't hit me).

What? There was an athletic peach here all this time? Well, the first time, I was small when I hit the block, and the second time, I didn't even hit that block at all. This'll probably make searching for secrets in this level easier!
Goal tape average so far: 956 / 28 = 34.143 stars each.
NOOOOO!!!

Argh! I hate that, and I usually try to avoid having that happen. If you spin jump onto an enemy that's overlapping something you can stand on like that, it's likely the game will see you land before checking for your collision with the enemy, and by that point, you're no longer spinning, so you get hurt.
Also, I wonder why the red shell isn't perfectly mirroring the blue shell, and is gradually getting further and further out of sync...
"Tick" +1 graze.
Well, that was totally a terrific use of the control coin! (Honestly, I was expecting that block to contain a vine.)
I really don't want to deal with two evil chairs at once. Let's try having only one evil chair present as I'm trying to do this.
I'd better be careful around those acorns, as they're basically donut lifts.
Umm... But won't I need a P-switch for this to be useful? And I haven't seen any P-switches in this level... Maybe there was one hidden somewhere that I somehow missed.
Which of those four levels will I be playing next time? Place your votes, and we'll find out next time! (There's a good chance I'll be fighting at least one boss next time!)
Alright, the control coin has expired. Now, I wonder if I can jump far enough to at least see the opposite side...
That took a while, but the red shell ended up winning!
Nope, time to Start+Select and try again. Let's see if I can find a P-switch somewhere...
I wonder if I can put together a big enough stomping combo to get glitched results from Wigglers here...
Goal tape average so far: 996 / 29 = 34.345 stars each.

What?! You can't slide-kill Big Boo in this hack? Okay, I understand the hacker not wanting me to cheese Big Boo like that, but if something like this is different from how it normally would work in the original SMW, I think it would be a good idea to inform the player of such a change ahead of time.
Aw, the waiting game sucks. Let's play Hungry Hungry Hippos!
Hi! Welcome Back! Voting results now!
I wonder if the parachuting enemy generator tends to favor one side over the other...
Well, I guess I'll just take the normal exit now, and use the control coin correctly on the next visit.
Hmm... I may need to take another look around the level.
Haha, very funny with that last block.
ARGH!!!
Aha, I've reached the other side... and it's populated by more evil chairs! Whoa!

You know... Those evil chairs have a similar movement pattern to those evil homing bullets I loathe so much. However, I guess these are more tolerable because they don't move quite as quickly, and they stop moving if I get far enough away from them.
Alright, I've made a modification to this tie-breaker room. The blue shell represents Wigglers Dwelling, while the red shell represents Haioku. Which one will win?

The gap in the coins there makes me think something will be hidden there, but... nope. (If there was a hidden block there though, it would potentionally cause that invisible solid block glitch if was hit before the top-center coin was collected.)
That unlocks a path back to Yukkuri Take. Now for the secret exit... (I'll ludicrously speed up most of the footage of me repeating the level.)
And here we have Flying Wigglers from Yoshi's I-- Whoa, holy crap! NO! GET AWAY!!!

By the way, does anyone know of an English-to-Samoan online translator? I wanted to put the phrase "And now, ludicrous speed bonus game!" in Samoan back there, but Google Translate doesn't have Samoan in its list of languages, and I can't seem to find any other translator program that does.
Mmm... Slanty...
There's some lag here, but I don't think it's too bad yet. Also, I have no need for a mushroom right now.
Okay, there we go! And there's the P-switch I was looking for! Now, let's race to the control coin block!
So, Haioku's next! Does it mean "high-octane gas"? Or "deserted house"?
Yes, there's the secret exit!
Hey, what are you doing here, Snifit? You're not a Wiggler.
Oh, there's the goal. However, I see something down below. Maybe a path to the secret exit?
Whoa, that was risky! If I stomp a Flying Wiggler here, it could be all over for me!
BGM: CUSTOM - Boo is taking over!

Oh, did I despawn it? ...Good. Whew! Alright, let's not stomp any more Flying Wigglers, because they WILL be out for blood if they get angry! (Wow, they're way more aggressive than in Yoshi's Island!)
Master combo! (7 hits)
What? Flying Wigglers can't be star-killed? Well, then I'd better book it out of here before my star wears off!
Looks like I'm in a vertical area filled with boxed-in Snifits now.
Sure, why not? The Boo was in my way.

And yep, I can start getting glitchy results that add to my coin counter now. But, I think that's enough of that. There's no score in this game, so all I'd get from that point on are more coins. Also, I don't want to stick around there forever.
It also allows me to score more coins from this multi-coin block. Of course, it would've helped if I'd faced to the left first so that the Big Boo wouldn't bother me...
That's it? Just eight coins? Is there nothing else up here?
Huh, red Snifits here shoot out 3-way fireballs. Still not nearly as dangerous as angry Flying Wigglers, though!
Shut up, clock.
BGM: Touhou 6 - Meiling's Theme - Shanghai Alice of Meiji 17
That unlocked Boss - Monkey Kong, and it doesn't look like the game will let me just walk past this level.
To be continued...
OH, YES!!!
Whoa, two evil chairs in a row, but that's nothing I can't handle.
BGM: Mega Man 9 - Hornet Dance
The coins spell "KID". I wonder if that has any significant meaning...
That was actually risky. What if I couldn't spin jump on the evil chairs?
Destroy the evil chair! ...Darn, I can't, probably because it's not actually evil. Also, this place isn't completely deserted, as there are ghosts here. Umm... Ghosts can count as residents, right?
So, the available levels to choose from with your votes this time are: Boss - Monkey Kong, Yōsu No Tera 2 *, Boss - Waru Bōrei, and Yoshi's Mountain.
At least the grounded Wigglers aren't really a threat, even when angry, and it looks like I have to stomp and ride them here.
Ooh, perfect! By using this vine and some screen scrolling to make the Wiggler to my left respawn over and over, I can make my stomping combo as large as I want!
BGM: Pokémon Ruby/Sapphire/Emerald - Route 110 (and Route 117, the non-desert parts of Route 111, Route 112, and the western part of Route 118)

Looks like the screen keeps scrolling up here. Hmm... I wonder if there's anything way up above that I could reach with the athletic peach. I'll have to remember to come back here and check that later.
That unlocked Yōsu No Tera 2 *, which I'm sure I'll learn the meaning of eventually. Now, let's head on over to the other level that tied for first place, Wigglers Dwelling!
Actually, I like the idea of seeing that happen for "dud" ? blocks, instead of the block just being plain empty.
Nothing up there, but I had to check. Ooh, there's our first Wiggler.
Yep, I can certainly go beyond "1-up" doing this!
I see stuff up there. Maybe I can get a boost from an evil chair?
Okay, this time I'm not gonna totally screw up with the control coin!
Yeah, I can easily tell the evil chairs apart from the normal ones, as the evil ones float slightly above the floor before they start moving.
11.05-life combo! Killer combo! (13 hits)
Goal tape average so far: 1034 / 30 = 34.467 stars each.
Looks like I'd have to bounce off of a Flying Wiggler to reach those 15 coins. Umm... No, thanks.
Ehehe... I wonder what raocow's reaction to this Big Boo would be?
Remember: DO NOT tick off the Flying Wigglers!
Nuts, looks like "deserted house". I was kinda hoping for "high-octane gasoline", even though I knew "deserted house" was much more likely.
Ooh, nice. I like how the bonus game gives you a free mushroom, in case you need it. Now, let's see if I can get those moons again...
Huh. You can slide-kill evil chairs. Good to know. (It's ironic that you can kill evil chairs by being in a sitting position. (Did I use the term "ironic" correctly there?))
More Boos in blocks, but there's a power up here too, which I can definitely use.
Yeah, I saw the possibility of doing this up-and-over maneuver last time.
Sure, whatever. Hey, Mr. Big Boo, can you help me reach that ? block over there? Thank you!
Oh, I guess I could've just bounced up there with the springboard. Well, whatever.
